data.text:
Grading policies for used cd,dvd and vinyl

SS Still Sealed /Nuovo sigillato

Vinyl/CD/DVD : never opened. Flawless, with no damage whatsoever.

M- Mint Minus /Copertina e cd-vinile-dvd come nuovo

Vinyl/CD/DVD : has been opened, but is still flawless

with no damage whatsoever; no visible marking, plays perfectly.

VG+ Very Good Plus / Copertina e cd-vinile-dvd ottimo

Vinyl: May have scuff marks and signs of some wear but

will still play almost perfectly throughout, with only

"barely detectable" crackles or pops. A slight noise at the

begining is allowable, but the remainder must be nearly flawless. Definitely no scratches or gouges that a touch with a dry finger can feel.

CD/DVD: may have some scuff marks and lights signs of some wear.

Cover: May only have the slightest signs of normal wear.

VG Very Good / Copertina e cd-vinile-dvd buono

The majority of records (worth selling) fall under this grade.

Vinyl: May crackle, pop or make other annoying noises, but only

occasionally,never continuously, and not more loudly than the

music being listened to.

CD/DVD:used with scuff marks and lights signs of normal wear. Visible scratches but plays perfectly all the way through

Cover: Normal used cover wear such as ring wear and split seams.

If there is abnormal damage such as tears or markings,

but the seller still feels that it qualifies as a "VG",

the damage must be described in comments attached to the item.

G+ Good Plus

Vinyl: May have continuous crackles, pops, etc... but not so loud as to

make the music completely unlistenable or unenjoyable to the

casual listener. Might also have "nasty little scratch" causing popping on one or two more songs, with the rest of record playing fine.

CD/DVD: used with marks and signs all over; it plays.

Cover: More than normal wear and tear.
